ichenden Gemeinschaftswillen erschließt die Sünde als Abkehr vom Wort.  aThis study approaches Luther’s hamartiology by way of the relatively neglected Great Lecture on Genesis. The author integrates different research perspectives on sin to understand man’s turning away in the context of God’s attention, understood in Trinitarian terms. By viewing creation, reconciliation, and perfection as the manifestation of God’s will for the community of man, sin can be conceived as a turning away from the Word.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aSinxChristianityxHistory of doctrines. 4aAnthropologie. 4aRechtfertigung. 4aSchöpfungslehre. 4aSünde. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / Anthropology.2bisacsh  aSin.  aanthropology.  acreation.  ajustification.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2016 Part 1z978311076250108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2016z9783110485394oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruyterteBook-Paket Reformationz9783110551693oZDB-23-FJR0 cEPUBz97831104922860 cprintz978311049456340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311049411240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110494112423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110494112/original  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-076250-1  DG Plus DeG Package 2016 Part 1b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2016  aZDB-23-DGGb2016  aZDB-23-FJR